## dup() function

Returns the concatentation of `x` with itself. If input is an iterable, it MUST be finite!

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
export declare function dup(x: string): string;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  x | <code>string</code> |  |

<b>Returns:</b>

`string`

## Remarks

Also see the  transducer for achieving a different kind of value duplication.

## Example


```ts
dup("hello"); // "hellohello"
dup([1, 2, 3]); // [1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3]
dup(range(3)); // IterableIterator<number>

```
